folder: Middagh Street & Hicks Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Middagh Street, north side, west from Hicks Street; a view of buildings that existed prior to 1880. In 1929 some frames in this view were still standing.

1890.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Middagh Street & Hicks Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
74 Middagh Street, south side, west of Henry Street. This building housed Engine Co. No. 3, until 1869, when the volunteer fire-corp was replaced by a municipally paid system. It was subsequently converted into a 4-story family house. In 1875, it was purchased by Jacob Ring who converted the first floor into a store; it was demolished before 1929.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, another view.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Hicks Street & Middagh Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Hicks Street, west side, south from Middagh Street.  Also seen is Middagh Street, south side, west from Hicks Street.  The corner building in 1870 was occupied by the Henry Walters Grocery; prior to this it was a stable for the Williamsburg bakery. The building was still in use in 1929.
April 1925

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
